<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wind Power To Produce Million KW by 2000 In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 20 (Xinhua) -- China has been looking closely at
wind power as an important source of electricity, and expects it
to provide one million kw by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
According to a senior official with the Ministry of Electric
Power, China has developed 10 million small wind power generators,
with a total capacity of 20,000 kw.
</P>
<P>
China now has the capacity to produce 30,000 wind generators
annually, and built 15 large wind power generation fields with a
combined installed capacity of more than 30,000 kw.
</P>
<P>
The official noted that China will continue to carry out its
policy of developing small generators for individual families
living in border areas and remote regions who are not connected to
power grids.
</P>
<P>
The country is phasing out its plan to develop wind power in
provinces which are rich in wind resources and lacking in power
supplies. The official source said that China is abundant in wind
resources, and about two-thirds of the country is windy, with
total wind energy resources estimated at 253 million kw. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
