<HEADLINE> Swaziland Reduces Tariffs for S.African Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 20 (Xinhua) -- Swaziland has extended its
generalised system of preferences (GSP) to South Africa, the
Department of Trade and Industry (DTI) said here today.
</P>
<P>
DTI said in a statement the GSP was designed to assist
beneficiary countries in increasing and diversifying their
exports to Swaziland.
</P>
<P>
A large of number of South African exports would from March 1
qualify for reduced customs tariffs in Swaziland, said the
statement.
</P>
<P>
Swaziland and South Africa are members of Southern African
Customs Union, which also includes Botswana, Lesotho and Namibia.
</P>
</TEXT>
