<HEADLINE> Swan Lake Opens China's Opera And Ballet Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 20 (Xinhua) -- "Swan Lake", performed by the
Ballet Troupe of the Central Opera and Ballet Theater, marked the
opening of 1997's China International Opera and Ballet Year in
Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
Qiao Shi, member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee and
Chairman of the Standing Committee of the National People's
Congress (NPC), was present for today's performance, together with
State Councillor Li Tieying, who is a member of the Political
Bureau of the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
This year's activities are sponsored by the Ministry of Culture
and the Ministry of Radio, Film and Television, and are intended
to increase exchanges between China and foreign countries.
</P>
<P>
Opera companies and ballet troupes from the Democratic People's
Republic of Korea, Russia, Austria, Switzerland, and Israel will
perform classics like "Sleeping Beauty" and "Swan Lake" for the
Chinese audience.
</P>
<P>
The sponsors say that troupes will visit Shanghai, Tianjin,
Guangzhou, Shenyang, and other large cities.  
</P>
</TEXT>
