<HEADLINE> Xinhua International News Summary at 1615 GMT, March 20 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO -- Palestinian President Yasser Arafat arrived here today
on a lightning visit for consultations with Egyptian President
Hosni Mubarak on Israel's Har Homa Jewish settlement project in
Arab East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders' meeting, the second this month, came two days
after Israel sent in bulldozers to Har Homa, the site of a
6,500-unit new Jewish neighborhood in East Jerusalem, where the
Palestinians want to establish the capital of their future state.
</P>
<P>
They are expected to discuss how to confront Israel's practice
to change the Arab features of East Jerusalem, while Mubarak
warned Wednesday it is thrusting the peace process into "a new era
of violence."
</P>
<P>
HELSINKI -- U.S. President Bill Clinton and Yeltsin arrived in
Helsinki today for the 11th summit, the toughest since the end of
the Cold War.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin, who will pay a working visit to Finland after the
two-day summit, arrived about three o'clock p.m. local time. He
was greeted at the Helsinki Vantaa airport by Finnish President
Martti Ahtisari.
</P>
<P>
A welcome ceremony for Yeltsin was held at the airport.
</P>
<P>
Earlier today, a smiling Clinton got out of the plane in a
wheelchair that is first moved into a catering truck lifted to the
gate of the plane. He has to be driven to the hotel in a mini-van
instead of a limousine. His right knee was injured in a fall more
than one week ago.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. and Russian presidents will begin their formal talks
on Friday with NATO's expansion, arms control and the economic
relations high on the agenda. The most important subject is the
alliance's enlargement, which will change security order in
Europe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
