<HEADLINE> Russia Bids for 2002 World Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 20 (Xinhua) -- Russia, who has never host the
World Men's Basketball Championship, is making a strong bid for
the 2002 tournament.
</P>
<P>
"Moscow and possibly St Petersburg will stage matches, if
Russia wins the right to host the tournament," Sergei Chernov,
vice-president of the National Basketball Federation, was quoted
as saying.
</P>
<P>
The United States, Australia and Germany are the strongest
challengers to hold the championship. Other bidders include
Croatia, Malaysia, Japan and Iran, reports said. 
</P>
