<HEADLINE> At Least 5 Killed, 25 Injured in Quake in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 20 (Xinhua) -- At least Five people including
four women were killed and 25 others injured today in an
earthquake measuring 5.5 on the Richter scale, according to
informed sources today.
</P>
<P>
Besides the casualties, dozens of houses collapsed and hundreds
of animals were killed in Bajaur tribal areas, 550 kilometers
southwest of Peshawar, capital of Pakistan's North West Frontier
province, informed sources in Peshawar told Xinhua through
telephone.
</P>
<P>
The earthquake, which occurred at 1351 hours (local time)
today, was also felt in Quetta, capital of Baluchistan province,
and its surrounding areas, the sources said. But there has been no
reports of casualties in the area so far.
</P>
<P>
According to the preliminary analysis of Meteorological Station
in Peshawar, the epicenter was about 550 kilometers southwest of
Peshawar in Suleman Range, they said.
</P>
<P>
This was the second tremor that jolted Quetta in less than 22
hours after a moderate intensity quake measuring 4.5 on the
Richter scale had shivered the Quetta valley earlier on Wednesday
evening.
</P>
<P>
About 47 people were killed and 125 others injured in the
earthquake that hit the Quetta valley on February 28. The
earthquake measured 7.3 on the Richter scale.  
</P>
</TEXT>
