<HEADLINE> EC Approves Humanitarian Aid to Ecuador, Peru, Bolivia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 20 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission(EC)
announced Thursday it had approved humanitarian aid of a total
amount of ECU 1.84 million(2.1 million US dollars) for Ecuador,
Peru and Bolivia following a series of natural disasters in these
countries.
</P>
<P>
According to the European Community Humanitarian Office(ECHO),
which manages the aid, emergency humanitarian aid worth ECU
440,000 (501,600 US dollars) will be provided to Ecuador in order
to distribute food, water and medicines to people hit by a
prolonged period of drought in south-west of the country.
</P>
<P>
In Peru, ECHO will emergency humanitarian aid worth ECU
600,000(684,000 US dollars) for thousands of people rendered
homeless by heavy flooding and mudslides.
</P>
<P>
An amount of ECU 800,000(912,000 US dollars) has been approved
in order to supply medical and food aid, reconstruction material
and clothing to victims of floods, river flooding and landslides
caused by heavy rains in Bolivia during the last two months.
</P>
</TEXT>
