<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Africa Not to Withdraw Nationals in Zaire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 20 (Xinhua) -- South Africa is not yet
considering pulling its diplomatic representatives out of
Kinshasa, capital of Zaire, Spokesman for the Department of
Foreign Affairs Marco Boni said today.
</P>
<P>
There are between 50 and 60 South Africans, including four
diplomats and their families, were believed to be in Kinshasa,
said Boni.
</P>
<P>
South African ambassador Jan van Deventer to the strife-torn
Zaire was still at the embassy in Kinshasa, and the embassy was
in constant touch with all nationals in the vicinity.
</P>
<P>
"There is no cause for alarm, contingency is in place but
there is no need to put them in place at the moment," said the
spokesman.
</P>
<P>
Tensions in Kinshasa are running high as Zairean rebels are
approaching to the capital, causing foreigners in the city flee
out of the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
