<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mobile Telecom Capacity to Hit 1.4 Million Ends in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 20 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai telecom authorities this
year will add one million ends into the city's mobile
telecommunication networks and develop 300,000 mobile phone
subscribers, according to sources from China's Ministry of Posts
and Telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
Having enjoyed years of speedy development, Shanghai this year
is to triple its mobile telecom capacity from 455,000 ends to over
1.4 million ends, registering a net increase of 975,000 ends. The
capacity of the city's analogue A and B mobile telecom networks
will add 155,000 new ends to 380,000 while the capacity of its GSM
networks is expected to be quadrupled from 200,000 last year to
800,000. The capacity of the newly introduced DCS1800 trial net is
to reach 220,000.
</P>
<P>
The city also plans to develop 300,000 new mobile phone users,
almost double the figure of 330,000 in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's mobile telecom businesses in the first two months
witnessed dynamic growth. The city in the period developed 30,094
mobile phone users, an average daily increase of 500 more users.
</P>
</TEXT>
