<HEADLINE> World Cup Rugby Sevens to Kick Off in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 20 (Xinhua) -- More than two decades after
hosting the first local seven-a-side rugby tournament, Hong Kong
has its dream come true on Friday when the Second World Cup Rugby
Sevens finals kicks off Friday in the Hong Kong Stadium.
</P>
<P>
It is nothing surprising now when Hong Kong was given high
comments on its efforts to have the game a world-class status and
bring the world's major sevens event to the city.
</P>
<P>
"During the past 21 years, Hong Kong has won a special place in
the lore of rugby football," said Leo Williams, Chairman of the
Rugby World Cup Ltd.
</P>
<P>
"The decision thus to award the second Rugby World Cup Sevens
tournament to Hong Kong was not only an overdue act of justice but
 also a recognition of Hong Kong's role in the elevation of the
Sevens code to international celebrity status," he added.
</P>
<P>
A brilliant field of 24 teams are to vie for the top honor of
the three knock-out championships - the Melrose Cup, the Plate and
the Bowel in the three-day competitions.
</P>
<P>
Among the line-ups are England, Argentina and Japan, the
winners of the Melrose Cup, Plate and Bowel championships at the
inaugural World Cup finals in Edingbourg, Scotland, in 1993.
</P>
<P>
England and Australia, winners and runners-up of the Melrose
Cup in 1993, and hosts Hong Kong are automatic qualifiers for this
year's World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
All the participating teams are split into eight pools of three
for a single round-robin play on the tournament's opening day on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The pool winners will be ranked first to eighth, the
second-placed teams will be ranked ninth to 16th and the
third-placed sides 17th to 24th.
</P>
<P>
The teams are to be split into eight groups of three again, for
another round of single round-robin competitions on the second day
on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
After the second single round-robin, the teams will be ranked
in the same manner as in the first round, with the pool winners
advancing to the Melrose Cup championship, the second-placed teams
to the Plate and the third-placed sides to the Bowl, all slated
for Sunday.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
