<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Southern Africa Urged to Set up Road Maintenance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, March 20 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's road haulers have
called on the Southern African Development Community (SADC) to
set up road maintenance funds to help the region to further
harmonize its transportation system.
</P>
<P>
Transport Operators Association executive officer Arther
Sandwith said here today while significant progress has been made
in embracing the requirements of the SADC protocol on transport,
SADC members should establish funds for road mending.
</P>
<P>
He said South Africa and Zambia are the only countries that
have already taken positive steps to establish such funds, urging
other countries in the 12-member SADC grouping to follow suit.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwe has already expressed its willingness to set up a
similar fund following recent proposals to establish road
authorities which would operate road tolls. 
</P>
</TEXT>
