<HEADLINE> U.S. to Help Africa Eradicate Polio </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 20 (Xinhua) -- The United States will
provide another 16 million U.S. Dollars to help eradicate
poliomyelitis in Africa by 2000, U.S first lady Hillary Clinton
announced today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the University of Cape Town, she said the latest
U.S. aid pledge to Africa reflected America's belief that the
future of Africa was inextricably linked to that of countries
throughout the world.
</P>
<P>
She spoke highly of democratic process in South Africa, saying
that she was deeply impressed by the patience and perseverance
with which South Africans were uniting to build a strong and
lasting democracy.
</P>
<P>
She arrived in South Africa on Tuesday for a four-day visit,
during which she will meet President Nelson Mandela.
</P>
<P>
Prior to her tour of South Africa, she visited Senegal.
</P>
<P>
After her stay in South Africa, she will visit Zimbabwe,
Tanzania, Uganda and Eritrea. 
</P>
</TEXT>
