<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Capable of Controlling Pests: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 20 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Agriculture
said today Ethiopia has the capability to ward off any resurgency
of pests.
</P>
<P>
Bateno Kabeto, the head of the Agricultural Development and
Crop Protection Department at the ministry, said his ministry has
the potential to control desert locusts, caterpillars and other
similar pests any time they emerge.
</P>
<P>
He noted that at present over 225,000 liters of pesticides,
sprayers and other equipment have been dispatched all over the
country.
</P>
<P>
In addition, regions in the country have stored over 485,000
liters of pesticides themselves.
</P>
<P>
He added that the East African Desert Locust Control
Organization and chartered airplanes from the Ethiopian Airlines
are responsible for spraying pesticides if the pests occur in the
regions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
