<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia to Curb Illegal Production, Transaction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 20 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Mining and
Energy of Ethiopia today said it has designed a mechanism by
which it could control the illegal production and transaction of
gold and other precious metals.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian News Agency reported that the prevalence of
illicit production and trade of the metal have been a major
constraint for the country to earn hard currency from the sector.
</P>
<P>
Thus a mechanism has now been designed so as to enable
pertinent governmental bodies to work jointly to curb the illegal
activity, said the report.
</P>
<P>
As most of the illegal producers and traders lack
understanding that they could be licensed, experts will be
deployed to sites to teach and organize the miners so that they
could get permits, said the ministry.
</P>
<P>
The ministry stressed the need to reinforce and train the
police force in the various mining sites with a view to
containing the illegal activities.
</P>
<P>
Over 1,000 kilograms of gold is produced illegally and
smuggled out of the country every year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
