<HEADLINE> Mandela Meets U.S. First Lady </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 20 (Xinhua) -- South African President
Nelson Mandela met visiting U.S. First Lady Hillary Clinton at
his official residence in Cape Town today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters after the meeting, Mandela said Mrs.
Clinton's visit to South Africa gave him an opportunity to thank
her first hand for the U.S. active support during his
anti-apartheid struggle.
</P>
<P>
South Africa has started programs including education projects
for members of disadvantaged communities, said Mandela.
</P>
<P>
Mrs. Clinton and her daughter Chelsea, escorted by
presidential adviser and ex-prisoner Achmed Kathrada, visited
earlier in the day Robben Island where Mandela spent 18 of his 27
years of imprisonment.
</P>
<P>
The Clintons arrived in South Africa on Tuesday for a four-day
visit. 
</P>
