<HEADLINE> Carlo Fassi Remembered at World Figure Skating </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAUSANNE, Switzerland, March 20 (Xinhua) -- Officials, skaters
and audience tonight stood up in silence to mourn Caro Fassi, a
well-known and respected figure in the skating community.
</P>
<P>
Fassi, who was the Chairman of the Coaching Commission of the
International Skating Union, died of a severe heart break at 67
this afternoon in a hospital in Lausanne, only hours before the
Men's free program competition of the 1997 World Figure Skating
Championships began.
</P>
<P>
Fassi coached many of the world's top skaters including Olympic
champions Peggy Fleming, Dorothy Hamill, John Curry and Robin
Cousins. He was born in Milan, Italy. As a skater, he won the
bronze medal in the 1953 World Championships and was twice
European figure skating champion, winning the gold in 1953 and
1954. 
</P>
</TEXT>
