for presidency. They are Charles Tayor of the National Patriotic
Front of Liberia, Alhaji Kromah of the United Liberation Movement
and George Boley of the Liberia Peace Council.
</P>
<P>
According to her, the peace process is expected to take a
major step forward today, with the inauguration of an electoral
commission.
</P>
<P>
The chairperson assured that peace process in Liberia remains
on course and appealed to countries still harboring Liberian
refugees to encourage them to return home and take part in
building a better country tomorrow. 
</P>
