<HEADLINE> Cyprus, Lebanon to Extradite Convicts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, March 20 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus, which has a large
proportion of foreigners in its prisons, and Lebanon will be able
to extradite convicts in a month, an official statement said today.
</P>
<P>
A protocol to the effect was signed in Beirut during the
current visit by Cypriot Justice and Public Order Minister Alecos
Evangelou, according to the statement.
</P>
<P>
The protocol contains the ratification documents from both
countries of a bilateral extradition agreement reached here in
1994.
</P>
<P>
Speaking after the signing of the protocol, Evangelou and his
Lebanese counterpart Rabige Tabbarah said the agreement will
initiate a broader cooperation in legal matters between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
According to official figures, 33 percent of the convicts in
the prisons of Cyprus are foreigners. 
</P>
