<HEADLINE> Abu Dhabi International Defense Exhibition Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, March 20 (Xinhua) -- The Third International
Defense Exhibition (IDEX-97) ended here this evening with the
United Arab Emirates (UAE) signing several arms contracts worth
163 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Besides the contracts, the UAE also concluded a deal for the
purchase of aircraft worth 26.5 million U.S. dollars from France.
</P>
<P>
The five-day exhibition, in which the most up-to-date defense
equipment and weapons were showed, was participated by some 750
companies from 42 countries.
</P>
<P>
The inaugural ceremony of the exhibition was attended by 30
defense ministers and 60 military delegations embracing senior
military officials in charge of arms sales in various countries.
</P>
<P>
During the exhibition, several demonstrations with live
ammunition were held as well as naval shows in the artificial
canal and in the Zayid harbor by participating companies. They
displayed radar networks and other systems of defense patrol
boats and equipment.
</P>
<P>
The number of visitors during the five-day exhibition is
calculated at 75,000.
</P>
<P>
The IDEX-97, the third of a series that began in 1993, is
considered one of the largest defense exhibition in the world as
far as participating companies are concerned.
</P>
<P>
The IDEX-97 organizing committee has decided to hold the next
such exhibition in 1999. 
</P>
