HONG KONG, March 21 (Xinhua) -- The principle of "One Country,
Two Systems" constitutes one of China's national policies and is
not an expedient measure, said Zhou Nan, director of Xinhua News
Agency Hong Kong Branch.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with reporters from Xinhua and Hong Kong-based
Wen Wei Po to mark the 100-day countdown of Hong Kong's return to
her motherland, Zhou said the Chinese government is firmly
committed to the implementation of the Sino-British Joint
Declaration on the Question of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Zhou said, "Hong Kong's return to China not only marks the
beginning of a new era for the territory, but also represents an
important step in the process of the reunification of China and a
new phase of the rejuvenation of the Chinese nation," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that Hong Kong's handover is a major event in modern
Chinese history and world history as well.
</P>
<P>
He said that the current situation, whether in Hong Kong, on
the Chinese mainland and or in the rest of the world, is all
becoming increasingly favorable to Hong Kong's smooth transition.
</P>
<P>
"The international community and the Hong Kong people are more
confident than ever before about Hong Kong's future," he said.
</P>
<P>
There may still be some people trying to making an uproar, but
that cannot possibly affect the overall situation where the smooth
transition of Hong Kong is going on, Zhou added.
</P>
<P>
Zhou firstly attributed Hong Kong's present favorable situation
to Deng Xiaoping's concept of "One Country, Two Systems", noting
that more and more people in Hong Kong have faith in it.
</P>
<P>
Another fundamental factor in the realization of Hong Kong's
return to her motherland is the strength of today's China, which
is now completely different from what it was like before 1949.
</P>
<P>
And thanks to the economic reforms and opening up begun in the
late 1970s, China has become more powerful and prosperous, he
said.
</P>
<P>
The old China was trampled upon by others, while today's China
is a powerful country which is no longer at the mercy of others,
thus enabling the Chinese government to resume the exercise of
sovereignty over Hong Kong without firing a shot, he said.
</P>
<P>
The fact that China maintains independence, is becoming ever
more prosperous and enjoys fast economic development toward the
21st century constitutes a fundamental basis for Hong Kong's
smooth transition as well as the territory's long-term prosperity
and stability, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that in the past 13 years, the central government of
China has set great store by the Hong Kong affairs. It has
resolutely implemented the Sino-British Joint Declaration on the
Question of Hong Kong and the Basic Law as well as the principle
of "One Country, Two Systems".
</P>
<P>
Zhou spoke highly of the work done by the Preparatory Committee
for the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) and the
Selection Committee for the First Government of the HKSAR in the
past year.
</P>
<P>
He said that with the basic completion of the work in the
preparations for the formation of the HKSAR government, Hong Kong
has brought about a culture of election featured with fairness,
justice and openness, adding that the elections suited to Hong
Kong's reality have received the acclamation from the Hong Kong
people.  
</P>
</TEXT>
