<HEADLINE> Jeanswest Fashion Design Contest in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Two young female designers from
Hong Kong won First and Second Prize in the finals of the 97'
China Jeanswest Casual Wear Design Contest in Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
The contest, first held in 1993, is sponsored by the China
Garment Association and Jeanswest International Co. It has
attracted 617 fashion designers from 25 cities and provinces in
China's inland areas, and for the first time this year, from Hong
Kong, according to Xu Bobo, director of the judges panel.
</P>
<P>
"Casual wear is claiming a larger part of the Chinese garment
market in recent years, with increases both in production and
sales," Xu said.
</P>
<P>
"But Chinese designs, production standards, and market
promotion of these kinds of clothes still leave a lot to be
desired," she added.
</P>
<P>
The contest is intended to cultivate new fashion designers,
introduce casual wear trends in production and sales, and increase
exchanges between fashion and design circles in China's inland
areas and in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Six prize winners will be given a one-week-trip to Hong Kong to
attend a garment festival there in July.
</P>
<P>
China's domestic markets have been selling more casual wear as
the quality of life improves, said Yeung Chun Fan, vice-president
of the Glorious Sun Group (Hong Kong), the major shareholder in
Jeanswest.
</P>
<P>
He said that Jeanswest, which has 270 stores already in the
country's inland areas, plans to open 1,000 more in 100 cities
over the next five years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
