<HEADLINE> China's First Qualifying Exam for Auctioneers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 21 (Xinhua) -- China held its first qualifying
exam for auctioneers in Shanghai today, with 131 auctioneers from
around the country sitting for it.
</P>
<P>
China's first batch of licensed auctioneers will be come from
these examinees.
</P>
<P>
The examination was held by the Ministry of Internal Trade and
the Ministry of Personnel.
</P>
<P>
According to China's Auction Law, which went into effect on
January 1, auctions must be held by auctioneers, and the Ministry
of Internal Trade and the Ministry of Personnel have jointly
issued provisional regulations on the necessary qualifications of
these auctioneers, and an auctioneers qualifying exam committee
has been set up.
</P>
<P>
Auction houses that operate without licensed auctioneers will
not be allowed to handle any auctions in the future.  
</P>
