<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Talks About Agricultural Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Jiang Chunyun,
speaking on agriculture today, urged Chinese officials in charge
of agriculture to get a better understanding of the current
agricultural situation to ensure stable and substantial
development.
</P>
<P>
During the past few years, China has seen favorable growth in
its agriculture, said Jiang, also a member of the Political Bureau
of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, many problems still exist. Some parts of the
country have ignored agriculture, reducing investment in
production, stopping preferential policies, reducing local
farmland, and imposing unreasonable charges on farmers.
</P>
<P>
And government sources report that China still has a total of
58 million people who do not have sufficient food or clothing.
</P>
<P>
Agriculture should be given priority in the country's economic
construction, Jiang said, and China will continue to increase
reforms in rural areas, improve the agricultural economy, increase
the use of science and technology, improve productive conditions,
and protect the ecology and environment.
</P>
<P>
Grain production and prevention of disasters are to be given
priority to ensure a good harvest this year, Jiang said, and
provincial governments should pay attention to local democratic
and legal systems that can see to it that rural people enjoy a
stable life.
</P>
<P>
Today's meeting was sponsored by the Propaganda Department of
the CPC Central Committee, the General Political Department of the
People's Liberation Army (PLA), and working committees of the
central organizations. 
</P>
