He emphasized the need for close contact and constant
consultations between the two countries at all levels on
bilateral, regional and international issues of mutual interest.
</P>
<P>
In particular, Leghari laid stress on further accelerating the
pace of development of bilateral economic relations.
</P>
<P>
Velayati, who arrived here today on an official visit to
Pakistan, handed over a written invitation from Iranian President
Akbar Hashemi Rafsanjani inviting President Leghari to the eighth
regular Summit of the Organization of Islamic Conference scheduled
to be held in Iran later this year.
</P>
<P>
Velayati said that Iranian leadership has strong interest in
strengthening the special relationship with Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan and Iran shared common views on major international
issues and always supported each other in multilateral fora, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Velayati also felicitated the president and the people of
Pakistan on the 50th anniversary of Pakistan's existence as a
sovereign state.
</P>
<P>
Leghari said he was looking forward to the visit of President
Rafsanjani to Islamabad to participate in the Extraordinary OIC
Summit being held on March 23 to mark Pakistan's Golden Jubilee
celebrations.
</P>
<P>
Pakistani Foreign Minister Gohar Ayub Khan and Foreign
Secretary Shamshad Ahmad were also present on the occasion.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
