<HEADLINE> Tung Chee Hwa Appoints Exco Members to Tackle Livelihood issues </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR) Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa today
announced that he has invited three SAR Executive Council members
to help him in mapping out long-term strategy in the areas
concerning the people's livelihood.
</P>
<P>
These members are Leung Chun Ying, who will look into housing;
Leung Kam Chung, who will be looking at education; and Tam Yiu
Chung, who will be considering services for the elderly.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference here, Tung said the three men
will work together with relevant government officials in
generating ideas through a critical analysis of opportunities and
challenges.
</P>
<P>
"These three members and government officials will put forward
their views in helping me to devise these policies. It is an
informal set-up. With close co-operation between these members and
 government officials, I am sure we will strike the right balance
between continuing our well-tried policies and looking for
constructive and innovative changes," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said he expected the three members to deliver their
respective recommendations by June this year.
</P>
<P>
"There are other areas of our community which I am very
concerned about, such as our future industrial focus and our
economic vitality, and in these areas we are still trying to look
at ways to move forward," he said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that this is not a move toward a ministerial or
semi-ministerial system of government. "This does not deviate from
 the terms of reference of the Executive Council in providing the
Chief Executive with informed views on various policy matters," he
 said.
</P>
<P>
"I hope close co-operation in these areas will help to realize
our long-term goals in the best interests of Hong Kong," he
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
