<HEADLINE> Switzerland to Grant Forestry Assistance to Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Switzerland has agreed to
provide a grant assistance of about 2.8 million US dollars to
Nepal for implementing the third phase of a community forestry
project.
</P>
<P>
The project, which has been named "Nepal-Swiss Community
Forestry Project", focuses on sustainable management of natural
resources with a view to raising the living standard of people in
the hilly area about 80 kilometers east of Kathmandu, according to
the Nepali Finance Ministry today.
</P>
<P>
Under the project, local user groups will be involved in
forest-related activities for balanced and sustainable social,
economic and environmental development.
</P>
<P>
An agreement on the grant was signed here today by respective
representatives of the two governments, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
Switzerland provided grant assistance for the implementation of
the previous two phases of the project, it added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
