<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Drive To Develop Marine Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 21 (Xinhua) -- During its Ninth Five-Year Plan
(1996-2000), China will concentrate on the major areas of marine
technology and improving it with science and technology, said a
government official here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters, Liu Yanhua, director of the social
development department of China's State Science and Technology
Commission, said, "In the area of marine technology, we will
concentrate on the fields of marine monitoring technology, marine
biology, and the exploitation and development of marine resources."
</P>
<P>
By the year 2000, China will try to develop high technology in
such areas as marine surveys, the demarcation of marine special
economic zones, and the exploitation of marine oil and gas
resources, to improve their technological level.
</P>
<P>
China will try to make major breakthroughs in the comprehensive
utilization of seawater resources and the utilization of seashore
environmental resources, and begin evaluating resources at the
south pole and in the continental shelf area.
</P>
<P>
China will improve its marine industry with science and
technology in the fields of marine farming, processing of marine
biological resources, utilization of marine chemical resources,
and direct utilization of seawater.
</P>
<P>
Over the past decade, the country has had some achievements in
offshore natural gas and oil development, marine biological
engineering, deep-water mining, acoustical technology, and
aquiculture, and it has learned how to cultivate kelp, prawns, and
shellfish on a large scale, thanks to developments in genetic
engineering, putting its marine cultivation in the first place in
the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
