<HEADLINE> China-France Economic Symposium Ends in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Chinese and French entrepreneurs
exchanged views on space technology, industrial automation,
telecommunications management, and investment on public facilities
during a two-day symposium on the economies of China and France in
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
At today's conclusion, head of the China Council for the
Promotion of International Trade, Guo Dongpo, said that over the
past two days the two sides have discussed cooperation on certain
practical projects, and that the symposium has achieved its goal.
</P>
<P>
Chinese entrepreneurs got a better understanding of France's
advanced technology and expertise in various fields, while their
French counterparts learned more about specific areas that China
wants to improve through international cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He said that China will continue to focus on primary industries
like agriculture, energy, transport, telecommunications, and the
housing industry, and that "We hope that French businesses will
pay more attention to the central and western parts of China and
to developing infrastructure to open up new fields of cooperation."
</P>
<P>
"The symposium is one of important activities carried out by
economists from the two countries. We wish to further strengthen
cooperation with the France-China Committee, and continue to hold
the symposium in a more effective way, to provide more and better
opportunities for the enterprises of the two countries in their
cooperation," he said.
</P>
<P>
Former French Premier Raymond Barre said that there are many
fields in China where French enterprises can cooperate with their
Chinese counterparts, and that they can offer China technology and
help.
</P>
<P>
The head of the France-China Committee, Jean-Pierre Desgeorges,
added that developing cooperation between small businesses is of
great importance to the establishment of long-term economic and
technological cooperation between the two countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
