<HEADLINE> Australian Shares close Slightly Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Australian shares retraced
morning gains to close slightly lower today.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark all ordinaries index closed 4.9 points lower to
2,386.4, off a high of 2,392.5 and a low of 2,378.8.
</P>
<P>
Early gains by BHP ahead of its profit announcement led the
market higher in morning trade before BHP retreated to close three
cents higher at 17.16 Australian dollars (13.47 US dollars) on
turnover of 5.2 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Banks defied the general downward trend, with the related index
closing up 35.6 points at 4,083.8, Westpac's shares closed 21
cents higher, the ANZ closed up 22 cents, while NAB closed down
nine cents.
</P>
<P>
The all resources index closed 0.9 points lower at 1,363.5
while the all industrials index was 9.7 points lower at 3,718.9.
</P>
<P>
National turnover was 335.73 million shares changing hands
worth 1.205.52 million Australian dollars (940 million US
dollars).  
</P>
