<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Ends Weaker As US Players Enter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, March 21 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar closed
weaker today as speculative players from the US entered the local
market and sold the currency.
</P>
<P>
The local unit ended at 78.40 US cents from 78.73 at Thursday's
close. It reached a low of 78.25 US cents.
</P>
<P>
Citibank trader Chris Wray said the currency fell dramatically
when the speculative US player entered the market.
</P>
<P>
The local currency is now almost two US cents lower than its
closing level just one week ago.
</P>
<P>
On the cross-rates, the Australian dollar closed at 96.84 yen
from 96.65 yen against the Japanese yen and at 1.3235 marks from
1.3252 marks against the Deutsche Mark.  
