<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arafat Condemns Bombing Attack in Tel Aviv </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian National Authority
(PNA) President Yasser Arafat has condemned the suicide bombing
attack in Tel Aviv today, which left at least four people died and
more than 40 wounded, Israel Television reported.
</P>
<P>
Arafat made the condemnation in a telephone conversation with
Israeli President Ezer Weizman, shortly after the bombing attack
took place.
</P>
<P>
The explosion occurred around 13:45 p.m. local time (1045GMT),
at Apropo coffee shop around the corner of Ben Gurion Street and
Adam Hacohen, just one block from Dizengoff, where a suicide
bombing attack took place one year ago.
</P>
<P>
Israel Television quoted police sources as saying that
according to an identity card found beside a dead body, the
suicide bomber was from the West Bank village of Tzurif.
</P>
<P>
However, no more details were given.
</P>
<P>
People in the coffee shop at the time of explosion said that
they saw a suspect came to the middle of the shop, before they
heard the sound of explosion.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli military authorities imposed a total closure of the
West Bank and Gaza shortly after the explosion amid mounting
tension with the Palestinians, Israel Television reported.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Israeli Internal Minister Avigdor Kahalani blamed
Arafat for giving the green light to the terrorist attacks
against Israeli targets. However, many political analysts doubt
about Arafat's ability to control the situation if tension fails
to be eased.
</P>
<P>
The explosion occurred at a time when tension is rising
between Israel and the Palestinians, after the construction of a
Jewish neighborhood in Jerusalem started Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The military and intelligence authorities have repeatedly
warned against possible Palestinian violence, but apparently the
warning was not heeded duly.
</P>
<P>
Dozens of Palestinian youths hurled rocks at soldiers in the
West Bank town of Bethlehem and similar confrontations also took
place in the West Bank town of Hebron this morning.
</P>
<P>
Several people were reportedly injured in the clashes.
</P>
<P>
While expressing his condolence over the dead in Tel Aviv
blast, Arafat also mentioned the casualties in the West Bank towns.
</P>
<P>
He hoped the injures, Israelis and Palestinians alike, would
recover soon, according to a CNN report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
