<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Jewelry Show Opens Doors to Asian Markets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong reinforced its role
as Asia's leading jewelry sourcing center when 12,040
international buyers flocked to the 14th Hong Kong International
Jewelry Show on March 12-15, organizers said today.
</P>
<P>
The annual jewelry extravaganza, featuring 619 exhibitors from
26 countries and regions this year, occupied 18,500 square meters
in the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center (HKCEC).
</P>
<P>
The show was jointly organized by the Hong Kong Trade
Development Council (HKTDC), the Hong Kong Jewelers' and
Goldsmiths' Association, the Hong Kong Jade and Stone Manufactures
Association, the Hong Kong Jewelry Manufacturers Association and
the Diamond Importers Association.
</P>
<P>
In spite of a significant increase of buyers from Europe and
the United States, the fastest attendance growth was from Asian
countries, said C.S. Lee, HKTDC's assistant executive director for
exhibition.
</P>
<P>
"This confirms that Hong Kong is the best possible place to
exhibit and gain access to the fast-developing Asia-Pacific
markets," Lee said. "Economic growth in this region is the
world's fastest, creating a spiral in demand for well designed
fine jewelry," he added.
</P>
<P>
The 15th Hong Kong International Jewelry Show, scheduled for
March 18-21, 1998 in the new extension part of the HKCEC, is
expected to be bigger and better, TDC said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
