<HEADLINE> Dalai's Taiwan Tour Criticized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 21 (Xinhua) -- The Dalai Lama's visit to Taiwan
will not be an ordinary religious pilgrimage, but a political
crusade to split the motherland plotted by forces of "Taiwan
independence" and "Tibet independence."
</P>
<P>
In a symposium held by China Tibetology Research Center today
in Beijing, scholars from the research center, the Central
University of Ethnic Minorities, the Chinese Academy of Social
Sciences, and so on made their analyses and criticism of Dalai's
splitting activities.
</P>
<P>
Doje Cedain, director general of the China Tibetology Research
Center, said China's reunification is making significant progress
as the return of Hong Kong and Macao approaches.
</P>
<P>
But the Taiwan authorities are also accelerating their pace of
creating "two Chinas" or "one China, one Taiwan," he noted, adding
that under such circumstance, the Dalai's visit to Taiwan will
make the forces of "Tibet independence" and of "Taiwan
independence" echo each other, and hinder the reunification.
</P>
<P>
Scholars including Huang Hao, research fellow of the Chinese
Academy of Social Sciences, said the invitation made by the Taiwan
authorities to the Dalai, who has been engaged in splitting the
motherland for a long time, provides him with an opportunity to do
splitting activities in the Chinese territory.
</P>
<P>
This shows that the Taiwan authorities are colluding with the
Dalai's group and going farther down the path of splitting the
motherland, they added.
</P>
<P>
Participants to the symposium also pointed out that if the
Dalai Lama wants to get rid of his situation of exile overseas, he
must abandon his concept of "Tibet independence" and stop his
splitting activities.
</P>
<P>
Any attempt between the Dalai Lama and the "Taiwan
independence" forces to split the motherland will be doomed to
failure, they said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
