<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets With Former Japanese LDP Head </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin,
who met with Obuchi Keizo, former vice-president of the Liberal
Democratic Party of Japan and his party, this afternoon, said that
this year marks the 25th anniversary of the normalization of
Sino-Japanese relations.
</P>
<P>
In those 25 years, development of bilateral relations was
generally good, but saw some interferences, Jiang said, adding
that "we hope to see normal development of Sino-Japanese relations
on the basis of the Sino-Japanese Joint Statement and the Treaty
of Peace and Friendship signed by the two countries".
</P>
<P>
He noted that healthy and stable Sino-Japanese relations are
significant for China and Japan, and for the peace, stability, and
development of Asia and the rest of the world.
</P>
<P>
In pointing out that past experiences, if not forgotten, can be
a guide for the future, Jiang said that "we should learn from
history, and view bilateral relations from a long-term and
strategic height, to make concerted efforts for the healthy and
steady development of Sino-Japanese relations".
</P>
<P>
Expressing his appreciation for the meeting with Jiang again,
Obuchi said he will continue to make efforts for Japan-China
friendship.
</P>
<P>
The president of the Chinese People's Association for
Friendship with Foreign Countries, Qi Huaiyuan, and vice-foreign
minister Tang Jiaxuan were present at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese visitors are here on a friendly visit as guests of
the China-Japan Friendship Association. 
</P>
</TEXT>
