<HEADLINE> China To Hold International Exhibition on Oceans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 21 (Xinhua) -- China's State Oceanic
Administration, the State Planning Commission, and the State
Science and Technology Commission have planned to hold the "97
Beijing International Exhibition on Ocean Resources Development,
Utilization, and Ocean Technology and Equipment" at the end of
November.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Dengyi, head of the State Oceanic Administration, said
that this is the first time for China to sponsor such an event on
the oceans.
</P>
<P>
The aim of the exhibition, he added, is to promote the
exploitation and utilization of ocean resources, speed up the
development of China's marine economy, display each country's
achievements in the fields of ocean resources utilization and
marine technology development, and expand international exchanges
and cooperation, as well as greet the upcoming Year of the Oceans.
</P>
<P>
Individual companies, research institutes, colleges, and
instituttions concerned with marine affairs from many countries
will be invited to the Exhibition, which plans to have a total
exhibition space of 80 million square meters, to deal with new
achievements, new technologies, and new equipment in the marine
industry. 
</P>
