<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tel Aviv Mayor on Blast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Tel Aviv Mayor Roni Milo has
told Israel Television that the blast in the city earler today
appeared to be a suicide bombing attack and suicide bomber himself
might also be killed in the explosion.
</P>
<P>
A bomb went off in a crowded coffee shop in the center of Tel
Aviv this afternoon, killing at least four people and injuring 34
others, Israel Television reported.
</P>
<P>
A man claimed to be member of the Islamic Resistance Movement
(HAMAS) has phoned Israel TV that his organization shoulders the
responsibility of the explosion which occurred around 13:45
p.m. local time (1045GMT), at Apropo coffee shop at the corner of
Ben Gurion Street and Adam Hacohen, just one block from
Dizengoff, where a suicide bombing attack took place one year
ago.
</P>
<P>
People, in the coffee shop when the bomb exploded, said that
they saw a suspect came into the shop, and went to the middle of
the shop before they heard the sound of explosion.
</P>
<P>
All injured people were evacuated to the nearby Ichilov
Hospital and Wofson Hospital, some of the seriously wounded have
been already gone under operation.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli security forces closed the area, fearing there
were more unexploded bombs.
</P>
<P>
The explosion occurred at a time when tension has been rising
between Israel and the Palestinians, after the construction of
a Jewish neighborhood in East Jerusalem started Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Israeli Defense Minister Yitzhak Mordechai said earlier that
he had been warned of plans for Palestinian violence today
in the Jerusalem area, after several dozen Palestinian youths
hurled rocks at soldiers in the West Bank town of Bethlehem.
</P>
<P>
There were similar confrontations between Israeli soldiers and
Palestinian youths in Hebron this morning, several people were
reportedly injured. 
</P>
</TEXT>
