<HEADLINE> Curfew Imposed in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, March 21 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan government
declared today a dust-to-dawn curfew would come into effect from
10:00 tonight in the country, according to a statement from the
Defense Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that with a view to curb any post election
violence and assist the police and the security forces in
maintaining law and order, at the conclusion of the polls to the
local authorities, curfew has been declared today with effect from
10 p.m. in the districts of Colombo, Gampaha and Kalutara in
Western province and from 11 p.m. in the other 14 districts in the
country.
</P>
<P>
This curfew will remain in force until 8 a.m. on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The statement added that the Defense Ministry has issued
instructions to the Police Department and the Armed Services to
impose this curfew most rigorously and take firm action against
any violators.  
</P>
