<DOCNO> XIE19970321.0118 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-21 13:22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Total Close Imposed on West Bank, Gaza </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Following a suicide bombing
attack in center Tel Aviv this afternoon, the Israeli army
immediately imposed a total closure on the West Bank and Gaza
Strip, barring Palestinians from entering into Israel, Israel
Television reported.
</P>
<P>
A bomb went off in a crowded coffee shop in downtown Tel Aviv,
killing at least four people and injuring more than 40 others.
</P>
<P>
The explosion occurred around 13:45 p.m. local time (1045GMT),
at Apropo coffee shop around the corner of Ben Gurion Street and
Adam Hacohen, just one block from Dizengoff, where a suicide
bombing attack took place one year ago.
</P>
<P>
Tel Aviv Mayor Roni Milo told Israel Television that it
appeared to be a suicide bombing attack, and the unidentified
suicide bomber himself might also be killed in the explosion.
</P>
<P>
People, in the coffee shop when the bomb exploded, said that
they saw a suspect came into the center of the shop, before they
heard the sound of explosion.
</P>
<P>
All injured people were evacuated to the nearby Ichilov
Hospital and Wofson Hospital, some of the seriously wounded have
already gone under operation.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli security forces closed the area, fearing there
were more unexploded bombs.
</P>
<P>
An unidentified man told the Israel Television that a member
of Hamas, the Islamic Resistance Movement, carried out the
attack, adding Prime Minister Binyamin Netanyahu's policy was
responsible for the bombing.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Israeli Internal Minister Avigdor Kahalani blamed
the Palestinian Authority President Yasser Arafat for giving the
green light to the terrorist attacks against Israeli targets.
</P>
<P>
Kahalani said that "If Arafat wanted to stop the terrorist
attack, he was able to do that."
</P>
<P>
However, political analysts here believed that the situation
might go out of everybody's control if no solution can be found to
defuse tension built up by Israel's policy of settlement expansion.
</P>
<P>
The explosion occurred at a time when tension has been rising
between Israel and the Palestinians, after the construction of a
Jewish neighborhood in Jerusalem started Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, Israeli Defense Minister Yitzhak Mordechai said
he had been warned of plans for Palestinian violence today in the
Jerusalem area, after several dozen Palestinian youths hurled
rocks at soldiers in the West Bank town of Bethlehem.
</P>
<P>
There were similar confrontations between Israeli soldiers and
Palestinian youths in Hebron this morning. Several people were
reportedly injured. 
</P>
</TEXT>
