<HEADLINE> China to Hold International Women's Basketball Series </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 21 (Xinhua) -- A three-leg internatioanl women's
basketball challenge series, participated by Ukraine, Russia,
Sough Korea and China, will be held in China from March 27 to
April 6.
</P>
<P>
The tournaments will be played in Jiaozuo, Henan Province,
Dongguan, Guangdong Province and Zhuji of Zhejiang Province
with a round-robin format each leg, the Chinese Basketball
Association (CBA) announced Friday.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time for the revamped Chinese team to play in
public after the Atlanta Olympic Games last summer when China
dropped to ninth place from second it won in Barcelona.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese women, coached by newly-named Zhu Jiazhi, include
2.04-meter center Zheng Haixia, who will play in American WNBA
next May, and other four Olympians.
</P>
<P>
"All the teams but Russia will send their internationals to the
series," said the CBA in a news release.
</P>
<P>
"Ukraine, European champion last year and fouth place in
Atlanta, is expected to be the biggest challenge to China," it
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
