<HEADLINE> Austrian Airlines to Add Flights to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Austrian Airlines announced today
that the air carrier will increase the flight frequency and add
one more destination to China so as to meet the increasing
business and tourist exchanges between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
According to Alfred Brader, general manager of Austria Airline
PRC Branch, his company is to increase the Beijing-Vienna flights
from two to three times a week.
</P>
<P>
The flight departs from Vienna every Sunday, Tuesday and
Thursday, then back to Vienna from Beijing every Monday, Wednesday
and Friday, with a stopover in Shanghai on the latter two flights.
</P>
<P>
He said that the flight increase is based on market analysis of
the past two years since the company started to run air routes to
China in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Also, the company has formed cooperative ties with Air China,
the country's largest international air carrier, on such issues as
terminal use and ticket marketing. Air China has agreed to send
Chinese air stewardness on board of Austria Airline's flights.
</P>
</TEXT>
