<HEADLINE> Beckenbauer Refuse to Run for FIFA Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, March 21 (Xinhua) -- World soccer legend Franz
Beckenbauer said here on Thursday that he would not seek election
to the FIFA president, according to reports reaching here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The remarks were made by the German on Swedish television and
ran counter to the wishes of current FIFA chief Joao Havelange,
who devoutly hoped Beckenbauer will take the position after his
retirment in 1998.
</P>
<P>
"I have decided not to be a candidate for the post of FIFA
President," Beckenbauer said, after meeting with the favorite for
the job UEFA's Swedish President Lennart Johansson in Geneva.
</P>
<P>
"I think it would be better for Europe if there was only one
candidate as otherwise it would split our vote," the 51-year-old
added. 
</P>
