<HEADLINE> Bankers Offer Loans for Shanghai's New Subway Line </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 21 (Xinhua) -- A group of Chinese bankers have
provided Shanghai's new subway project with 400 million yuan in
loans for its Pudong section.
</P>
<P>
This is the third time for the banking group to offer special
loans for the No.2 subway project. The loans now total 800 million
yuan.
</P>
<P>
The No.2 subway line is designed to link Hongqiao International
Airport with the Pudong New Area's international airport, which is
in the preparatory stages, via a tunnel under the Huangpu River.
</P>
<P>
Work is now being done on the Jing'an Temple to Pudong section,
according to local officials.
</P>
<P>
The banking group consists of the Construction Bank of China
Shanghai No.5 Branch, the Industrial and Commercial Bank of China
Pudong Branch, Agricultural Bank of China Pudong Branch, Bank of
China Pudong Branch, and Shanghai Pudong Development Bank Nanshi
Branch.  
