<HEADLINE> New Senate Chairman Elected in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Wasim Sajjad, nominee of the
ruling Pakistan Muslim League (N) (PML-N), was elected as chairman
of the Senate for the fourth consecutive term today.
</P>
<P>
Wasim won 49 votes while Masood Kausar, nominee of the PML-N's
arch rival People's Party of Pakistan (PPP), secured 13 votes at a
special session of the upper house of parliament held here this
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Out of the total 80 votes polled, 18 were declared invalid.
</P>
<P>
Wasim held this post from 1988 to March 20, 1997.
</P>
<P>
He also served as the president of Pakistan from July 19 to
November 13, 1993.  
</P>
