<HEADLINE> Polling Closed For Sri Lanka's Local Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Polling closed for Sri Lankan
local government elections with results expected to be announced
later tonight.
</P>
<P>
Over 9.37 million voters in 17 contested Election Divisions in
seven provinces throughout the country, except in the north and
east due to security reasons, are believed to have cast their
votes.
</P>
<P>
Today's voting lasted 9 hours from 7:00 in the morning till
4:00 in the afternoon.
</P>
<P>
President Chandrika Kumaratunga cast her vote in her native
town of Attanagalla, 35 kilometers East of Colombo, this morning.
</P>
<P>
A total of 18,586 candidates from 12 political parties and 136
independent groups have contested the 3,567 seats in 238 local
government bodies, of which 12 are municipal councils, 31 urban
councils and 195 village councils.
</P>
<P>
Today's polling was conducted under tight security maintained
by over 30,000 policemen and the army. Strict orders went to all
police divisions from police headquarters this morning to arrest
trouble makers.
</P>
<P>
There were several incidents of violence reported from some
areas, according to police sources here.
</P>
<P>
They said that the main complaints related to assaults on
polling agents.
</P>
<P>
A curfew may be imposed late in the evening, according to
informed sources here. 
</P>
</TEXT>
