<HEADLINE> India Revokes President's Rule in Uttar Pradesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Indian President Shanker Dayal
Sharma today revoked the imposition of president's rule in Uttar
Pradesh paving the way for the installation of a popular
government in the state, the Press Trust of India said.
</P>
<P>
President's rule was imposed in the most populated state on
October 17 last year after the state assembly election resulted in
a hung house.
</P>
<P>
Earlier the Indian cabinet had approved the revocation of
president's rule in the state on the recommendation of Uttar
Pradesh Governor Romesh Bhandari.
</P>
<P>
The president's rule was revoked because the Bharatiya Janata
Party and the Bahujan Samaj Party had decided to form a coalition
government, ending a five-month political stalemate in the state.
