<HEADLINE> India's Steel Exports Register Sharp Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 21 (Xinhua) -- India's total export of steel
during the first 11 months of the current fiscal year (from April
1996 to February 1997) was one million tons as against 731,000
tons during the corresponding period last year, an increase of
36.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
According to The Hindustan Times today, the total production of
steel during the period under review was 20.37 million tons as
against the production of 19.06 tons during the previous
corresponding period, showing an increase of 6.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
The total production of pig iron during the first 10 months of
the current financial year was 2.91 million tons, up 16 percent
from the production of 2.51 million during the corresponding
period last year. 
</P>
