<HEADLINE> Share Prices Fall Lower on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to fall
lower on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials Index declined by another 26.95 points to close at
2068.95 points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume was thin at 172.57 million units, worth
394.94 million Singapore dollars (about 278.13 million US
dollars). Declines overwhelmed advances by 267 to 72, while 268
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Sel Dredg was the most actively traded stock as it posted a
turnover of 16.24 million units. It was followed by Pacific Andes
which had 8.35 million shares traded. JSH 500 was next with 4.66
million of its shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Samanda Holdings topped the gainers' list of the day as it rose
by 60 cents to finish at 9.1 Singapore dollars. Thai Prime Fund
gained 55 cents to end at 10.5 US dollars, while Tong Meng was 24
cents higher at 5.2 dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Rothmans Malaysia was the biggest loser as it
declined by 14.82 dollars to end at 0.58 dollar. Local property
developer City Developments warrant98 and GE Life fell by one
dollar each to close at ten and 21.4 dollars respectively.
Creative 50 was 70 cents lower at 14 Singapore dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
