<HEADLINE> Indian Customs Officials Seize 8 Kgs of Gold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Eighty three gold bars worth
about five million rupees (about 143,000 U.S. dollars) were seized
by Indian customs officials in Mumbai (Bombay) airport early today
from three passengers, who arrived from Singapore.
</P>
<P>
According to Press Trust of India, a mother and her daughter,
settled in Austria, were picked up on suspicion and 65 bars,
weighting about 6.5 kilograms, were recovered from their personal
belongings, a customs official said.
</P>
<P>
In another case, a Malaysian national, who concealed 18 gold
bars, weighting about 1.5 kilograms in his shoes and socks, was
detained.
