<HEADLINE> Xinhua International News Summary at 0800 GMT, March 21 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE -- Both chambers of Yugoslavia's Federal Assembly on
Thursday approved an agreement to establish special cooperative
relations with the Bosnian Serb Republic singed last month.
</P>
<P>
CARACAS -- Venezuela's former president Carlos Andres Perez
Thursday launched a new political party and vowed to lead the
country to a political renewal. The party, known as the "Opening
and National Participation Movement," would break the current
political structure and obtain "a free Venezuela for Venezuelans,"
said Perez.
</P>
<P>
ROME -- Italian Defense Minister Beniamino Andreatta denied
that Italy was planning military intervention in neighboring
Albania to help restore order in the crisis-hit country.
</P>
<P>
HAVANA -- Eight soldiers and a civilian were killed and 24
injured on Wednesday evening in a head-on collision between a
Cuban military bus and a truck.
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The U.S. Senate today approved a resolution that
ends any chance for Congress to reject President Bill Clinton's
approval of Mexico's anti-drug efforts.
</P>
<P>
WARSAW -- Members of Poland's Solidarity Union ignored a
government offer and entered into their second day of protests
against the closure of the Gdansk shipyard Thursday. Despite the
heavy presence of riot police, nearly 2,000 union members took to
the street in front of the parliament building and the ruling
party's headquarters in this capital.
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- U.N. General Assembly (GA) President Ismail
Razali proposed today that the membership of the Security Council
should be increased from 15 to 24. Under the proposal, five new
permanent members and four non-permanent members are going to be
added to the Security Council.
</P>
<P>
BANGKOK -- The Stock Exchange of Thailand (SET) Board has
decided to increase capital requirements for those companies
seeking listing in a bid to promote a healthier bourse.
</P>
<P>
DHAKA -- Bangladeshi Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina Thursday met
with visiting Iranian Foreign Minister Akbar Velayati and agreed
to attend the 8th summit of the Organization of Islamic Conference
to be held in Tehran in next December. 
</P>
