<HEADLINE> NZ Stocks Finish Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, March 21 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
had an active day today, reversing the down trend experienced in
the past few days and ignoring the sharply lower close on Wall
Street overnight.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 index ended 17 points higher at 2230 with a turnover
 of 70 million NZ dollars (48 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Telecom shares rose 7 cents to 650 cents. They accounted for 40
percent of the total turnover. Air New Zealand A shares climbed
5c to 269c, and B shares edged up 2c to 397c as investors swopped
between the two shares in the wake of Australian Qantas Airways
selling its stake in the NZ company.
</P>
<P>
Among other leaders, Brierley Investment gained 2c to 137c,
Fletcher Paper went up 4c to 290c, Carter Holt Harvey jumped 7c
to 305c, and Lion Nathan declined 8c to 330c.
</P>
<P>
Overall, there were 53 roses and 34 falls.  
</P>
