<HEADLINE> Macao to Launch Campaign on Prevention of TB </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Macao is to stage a promotion
campaign to spread knowledge on the prevention of tuberculosis, a
infectious disease that has high incidence in the territory.
</P>
<P>
The government's Health Department said between March 24 and 29
it will hold lectures and education courses for students and
workers as well as local residents to help them catch the correct
information about the disease.
</P>
<P>
A patient with the disease coughs, has fever, becomes thin and
often sweats. He or she can pass on the disease to others through
the air.
</P>
<P>
About three million people die of the disease a year across the
world. In Macao, about 125 people out of every 100,000 catch the
disease annually, and five of them will die, local health
officials said.
</P>
<P>
Last February, the Health Department established a special
working team, composed of 12 doctors, psychologists and
sociologists, to carry out the promotion campaign.
</P>
<P>
The World Health Organization (WHO) has set March 24 as the
World Anti-Tuberculosis Day. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
