<HEADLINE> Uganda Has Six More Districts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, March 21 (Xinhua) -- The Parliament of Uganda
approved Thursday a proposal on the creation of six more
districts with 156 votes in favor, one against and three
abstentions.
</P>
<P>
The proposal was raised by Bidandi Ssali, the minister of
local government in the name of the cabinet.
</P>
<P>
The proposal suggested initially to create seven new
districts, but only six of them were ratified at Thursday's
session of the parliament.
</P>
<P>
The new districts are Sembabule and Nakasongola in the central
Buganda region, Adjumani in the north, Bukholi, Busia and
Katakwi in the east.
</P>
<P>
The proposed district of Koboko in the north was withdrawn
from the voting due to the dissidence on the name of the district
and the location of its headquarters.
</P>
<P>
The bill will take effect on July 1.
</P>
<P>
Uganda now has 45 districts. enditem


