<HEADLINE> Britain Backs Kenya's Peace Efforts for Zaire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, March 21 (Xinhua) -- British High Commissioner to
Kenya Simon Hemans has expressed support for Kenya's peace
efforts to seek a lasting solution of the crisis in eastern
Zaire.
</P>
<P>
Following talks on Thursday with Nicholas Biwott, Kenyan
Minister of State in the Office of the President, the envoy noted
that his government was encouraged by the Nairobi II summit held
on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that it was the desire of his government that
peace and tranquillity be restored in the troubled Zaire, the
Kenya Times reported today.
</P>
<P>
The British envoy said that he was pleased with the
determination of Kenyan President Daniel arap Moi who chaired two
Nairobi summits to find ways to stop the fighting in eastern
Zaire.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his hope that the impetus to search for a
peaceful solution in Zaire would be successful.
</P>
<P>
He noted that a ceasefire in the fighting between the Zairean
government and the rebels led by Laurent Kabila was vital so that
relief food and medicine may be transported to people in the
affected areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
