<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Saudi Arabia Beats Bangladesh 4-1 in World Cup Tie </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Arabia downed
Bangladesh 4-1 and Malaysia beat Chinese Taipei 2-0 in the Asian
qualifying matches for the 1998 World Cup soccer finals.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia and Saudi Arabia has each collected seven points with
the same record of two wins and one draw at the halfway stage of
the Asian Group One competition.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia will host the second leg of the tournament in
Jeddah from March 27. It remains favorite to take the single
qualifying spot to the main Asian qualifying tournament.
</P>
<P>
The Asian Cup champion, held 0-0 by Malaysia on Tuesday, was
again not on top form but good enough to beat the Bangladesh side,
who has lost all its first three matches.
</P>
<P>
Striker Khalid Al Mowalad opened the scoring at the 20th minute
and Khalid Al Temawi put it 2-0 five minutes later.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh skipper Mohd Jewel Rama converted a penalty spot in
the 41st minute to close the gap.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia pulled away with two goals through Abrahim
Shahrani in the 65th minute and Fahad Mehalel in 73rd.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia went ahead in the second minute through Cik Zambil
Ahmad, and Rosdee Sulong scored the second goal in the 16th
minute. 
</P>
</TEXT>
