<HEADLINE> Yugoslavia Intensifies Control over Border with Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, March 20 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslavia has taken measures to
safeguard security and stability of the border areas with Albania,
which has been engulfed in an armed unrest in the past weeks.
</P>
<P>
The Supreme National Defense Committee of the Federal Republic
of Yugoslavia has decided to close the borders with Albania in an
effort to prevent the inflow of refugees, a report from the
Yugoslav military said today.
</P>
<P>
The report said that Yugoslavia is intensifying efforts to
train young officers and staging a joint military exercise of the
air force and a special contingent of the frontier force along the
border.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of Albanians have fled the country over the past two
weeks, mainly to Italy, to escape the armed unrest erupted after
the collapse of the popular pyramid investment schemes in which
thousands lost their life savings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
