<HEADLINE> Zambian Firm Enters Eastern African Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, March 21 (Xinhua) -- TAP Building Products, one of the
largest manufacturing companies in Zambia, has started commercial
operation in Tanzania with an eye to fully exploit the market in
eastern Africa, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
TAP, Zambia's leading manufacturer of asbestos-cement roofing
materials, pipes and moulded goods, is the first private Zambian
company to entry into eastern Africa, said the reports.
</P>
<P>
TAP has set up a regional office in Dar es Salaam, the capital
of Tanzania. Its office is commissioned by Tanzanian Minister for
Industries and Trade William Shija, TAP Marketing Service Manager
Tim Walker was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The opening of the office will turn TAP into a leading
supplier of building materials to Tanzania and then help it
increase raw materials exports to Kenya and Uganda, said the
reports. enditem

