<HEADLINE> UK Pledges 1.66-M-U.S.-Dollar Aid to Great </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Britain has pledged 1.66
million US Dollars of refugee relief fund to the Great Lakes
region, a British High Commission press release said here today.
</P>
<P>
According to the release, among the fund, 1.6 million Dollars
have been allotted to the U.N. High Commissioner for Refugees,
224,000 Dollars to the World Food Program and 576,000 Dollars to
the International Committee of the Red Cross.
</P>
<P>
It added that Zaire and Rwanda would benefit more from the
assistance. 
</P>
