<HEADLINE> World Skiing Champion Skaardal Undergoes Knee Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Norway's double world
super-giant slalom champion Atle Skaardal underwent an
operation to remove bone thickening from his left knee here on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
According to local reports, Doctors said that 31-year-old
Skaardal, the winner of seven world cup events, would
wait several months to see how his knee responded to the
operation before making a final decision about continuing his
skiing career. 
</P>
</TEXT>
