<HEADLINE> ADB Grants Loans to Vietnam, Papua New Guinea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 21 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
announced here today that it will grant loans of millions of U.S.
dollars to Vietnam for rehabilitation of its degraded forests, and
to Papua New Guinea for a health development program.
</P>
<P>
In a press statement, the Manila-based bank said that with a 33
million dollar ADB loan, about 114,000 hectares of degraded
forests and bare lands in Vietnam will be rehabilitated under a
major reforestation project.
</P>
<P>
The reforestation project is scheduled for completion by 2003,
it said.
</P>
<P>
In Papua New Guinea, the bank said, women and children in rural
areas will be the major beneficiaries of a health sector
development program, for which the ADB has approved loans totaling
60 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The program focuses on "the provision of priority health
services for women and children in the rural areas and supports
improvements in the management and efficiency of the health
system," it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
