<HEADLINE> Brazil Launches 1997-1998 National Health Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, March 20 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian President Fernando
Henrique Cardoso today launched a 1997-1998 national health plan,
aiming at decentralizing health services and rationalize financial
resources.
</P>
<P>
He said an investment of 14.5 billion U.S. dollars is required
to implement the two-year plan.
</P>
<P>
The country's health spending would be increased 31.1 billion
dollars a year.
</P>
<P>
Of the 31.1 billion dollars, the government would contribute
20.3 billion and the states and municipalities would be
responsible for 6.2 billion and 4.6 billion respectively. 
