<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Business Leaders Urge Shifting of Weekly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, March 21 (Xinhua) -- A group of business leaders of
Bangladesh urged the government to change the official weekly
holiday from Friday to Sunday for the greater interest of boosting
business and trade activities both locally and internationally.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh's exporters and importers are losing business
transaction with foreign countries for two days in a week because
of the weekly holiday on Friday, the business leaders said in a
joint statement on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The statement, issued jointly by the Metropolitan Chamber of
Commerce and Industry, the Dhaka Stock Exchange, and the
Bangladesh Garment Manufacturers and Exporters Association, urged
the government to take immediate steps to change the weekly
holiday.
</P>
<P>
In September 1982, the then government of Bangladesh changed
the weekly holiday from Sunday to Friday.  
</P>
