will over time contribute to banking and monetary stability, debt
market development and home financing in Hong Kong."
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the composition of the board, Tsang said, "The
15-member board has a balanced representation with its directors
drawn from different sectors of the community."
</P>
<P>
Bankers, legislators, members of the consumer council and
senior officials from the financial and housing sectors were
included in the board.
</P>
<P>
Their initial one-year appointments began on Wednesday and will
run until the first annual general meeting of the corporation, due
to be held around March 1998.  
