<HEADLINE> Yugoslavia's Trade Deficit Declines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, March 20 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslavia's trade deficit in
February fell to 113 million U.S. dollars, down 125 million
dollars from the previous month, official statistics released
today show.
</P>
<P>
The government attributed the reduction to a fall in imports
caused by a shortage of foreign exchange and an increase in
exports to developed countries.
</P>
<P>
In the first two months of this year, export volume was 283
million dollars and import volume 634 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Exports to developed countries reached 125 million
U.S. dollars, up 69.7 percent over the same period last year.
</P>
