<HEADLINE> Lanzhou To Host 1997 Trade Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Lanzhou, capital of northwest
China's Gansu province, will host a trade fair from August 18 to
24 in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Since 1993, Lanzhou has succeeded in hosting four trade fairs,
which have become northwest China's windows on the outside
world. To extend the influence and attract more overseas
investment, approved by the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation, the provincial government and Lanzhou city will
co-sponsor the 1997 Lanzhou trade fair, which will be the largest
of its kind.
</P>
<P>
An official of the organizing committee says that, this trade
fair will focus on trade talks, inviting overseas investment,
commodity exhibition and technology exchange. The committee will
also hold an exhibition presenting achievements of Gansu's
economic and social development since 1949.
</P>
<P>
As the hometown of Dunhuang art, Gansu will also feature
activities like travelling and cultural exchange.
</P>
<P>
Besides the 13 regions and counties in Gansu, the organizing
committee has invited overseas investors and companies from other
provinces. The two exhibition halls will provide 1,800 exhibition
stalls for the investors.
</P>
<P>
Cui Zhenghua, deputy governor of Gansu, says that, the 1997
Lanzhou trade fair is an important activity for presenting Gansu
to the outside world. In August, Lanzhou will welcome guest
businessmen to its abundant natural resources, stable investment
environment, and promising projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
