<HEADLINE> Nepali PM Calls for Cooperation from All of Nation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Nepal's Prime Minister Lokendra
Bahadur Chand has called for cooperation from all political
parties and the ordinary people in the country.
</P>
<P>
In a statement broadcast by the state-run Radio Nepal Thursday
evening, Chand said that his coalition government, which came to
office last week, will create an atmosphere where every individual
can find right opportunities and realize potentials for his own
prosperity.
</P>
<P>
Noting that Nepal faces problems like the increasing number of
people living in poverty and the worsening employment situation,
the prime minister said the government's prime concern is how to
relieve the country of hunger, disease and poverty.
</P>
<P>
While stating that the country's future hinges on the planned
development of manpower and water resources, Chand stressed the
importance of political stability, which he said the newly formed
three-party government will help ensure.
</P>
<P>
The new government will take effective measures to bring the
rampant corruption, financial irregularities and smuggling under
control, he said, adding that administrative expenditure and
facilities for ministers will be cut down under the principle of
austerity.
</P>
<P>
He also pledged that the government will encourage the private
sector to play a role in areas like industry, tourism, commerce
and communications.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Chand concluded that the country lacks
cooperation, understanding and honest effort for development, and
he appealed to all of the nation to cooperate with his government
in its pursuit of the nation's interests and prosperity.  
</P>
