<HEADLINE> Kontic Reelected Yugoslav Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, March 20 (Xinhua) -- The Yugoslav parliament today
approved a second four-year term for Prime Minister Radoje Kontic,
who vowed that his new government would be devoted to a
modernized, democratic, legal and welfare-minded Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Addressing parliament, Kontic said that during his second term
the government would strengthen the country's status in the world
and strive for its return to the international community.
</P>
<P>
He said Yugoslavia would also try to complete the normalization
of diplomatic and economic ties with its former republics.
</P>
<P>
Kontic said that the new government would give priority to
establishing an open market economy, improving living standards,
increasing job opportunities and ensuring the social security.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the government's short-term task is to achieve
normal relations with international financial and trade
organizations.
</P>
<P>
The new Yugoslav government consists of four vice prime
ministers and 16 ministers, five more than the previous
government, including a minister for relations with international
institutions.
</P>
<P>
Kontic, a Liberal Party member, was elected prime minister for
the first time in February 1993. 
</P>
