<HEADLINE> Canada Provides Relief Aid to Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, March 20 (Xinhua) -- The Canadian government will
provide emergency relief aid worth a total of 360,000 U.S. dollars
to victims of the turmoils in Albania.
</P>
<P>
Canada's relief effort in Albania is in response to an appeal
by the Geneva-based International Committee of the Red Cross
(ICRC), said a news release from the government.
</P>
<P>
An estimated 10,000 adults and children in hospitals and
orphanages around the tiny Balkan nation will receive food and
medical assistance from Canada.
</P>
<P>
The emergency relief effort is amid a crisis brought on by
widespread individual financial losses prompted by the collapse of
nationwide fraudulent pyramid investment schemes.
</P>
<P>
Since then, there has been a general breakdown of law and order
in Albania, with cities in the south under the control of rebel
groups. 
</P>
</TEXT>
