<HEADLINE> Nearly 330 Kilos of Narcotic Drugs Seized in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, March 21 (Xinhua) -- A total of 329.8 kilograms of
narcotic drugs including 193.5 kilograms of heroin and 128
kilograms of opium was seized by the Myanmar authorities in
February, the official daily The New Light of Myanmar reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The seizure also included 214 liters of phensedyl and 401,612
pills of amphetamine.
</P>
<P>
The Myanmar authorities took action against 447 persons in 297
drug-related cases in the month, the report said.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, Myanmar seized a total of
2,080 kilograms of narcotic drugs including 504 kilograms of
heroin and 1,300 kilograms of opium in 1996 with 5,540 persons
apprehended in 3,771 cases.  
</P>
