<HEADLINE> Hainan to Improve Industrial Structure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, March 21 (Xinhua) -- China's southernmost Hainan
province will speed up contruction of 10 key projects this year,
in a bid to improve local industrial structure by developing its
leading industries in the fields of petrochemicals, automobiles,
foodstuffs, textiles, pharmaceuticals, paper pulp, and building
materials.
</P>
<P>
A natural gas fertilizer plant in Basuo is expected to complete
its second phase of construction, to form an annual production
capacity of 450,000 tons of synthetic ammonia and 800,000 tons of
urea. Nearly 15.6 billion yuan will be invested in setting up two
sets of fertilizer-production facilities in Yangpu.
</P>
<P>
A cement plant in Changjiang is expected to go into operation
this year to produce 820,000 tons of cement annually.
</P>
<P>
The province will build a floating glass plant to produce 2.7
million crates of plate glass this year, and a plant to produce
600,000 tons of paper pulp a year.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the 10 projects will include a plant to produce
800,000 km of fiber-optic cables annually, a oil refinery to
process six million tons of crude oil, a sugar refinery to press
8,000 tons of sugar cane, a plant to produce 520,000 tons of iron
and steel, and a plant to produce 140,000 tons of polyester chips.
</P>
<P>
Hainan province will take advantage of local rich resources to
build the 10 projects, some already under busy construction, to
give the local economy a boost. 
</P>
</TEXT>
