<HEADLINE> Qinhuangdao Ready For Tourism Boom </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINHUANGDAO, March 21 (Xinhua) -- North China's famous port
city of Qinhuangdao is well prepared for the 1997 tourism year.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the city received 6.47 million domestic tourists and
67,000 overseas tourists, up 24 percent and 124 percent over the
previous year respectively.
</P>
<P>
With its convenient position of being adjacent to the Bohai
Sea, Yanshan Mountain, Liaoning province, Beijing and Tianjin,
Qinhuangdao has abundant tourism resources.
</P>
<P>
Since 1978, Qinhuangdao has built ten tourism scenes with the
Great Wall and port area as its hallmarks. The Shanhaiguan and
Laolongtou parts of the Great Wall and Beidaihe beach were listed
among "China's top 40 tourism scenes."
</P>
<P>
Su Xipo, director of the city's tourism bureau, says that they
have taken efforts to ensure major uplifting.
</P>
<P>
Tourism attractions such as the Shanhaiguan Great Wall
festival, the international wetland birds conference, and a
mountain climbing competition will be held.
</P>
<P>
Winter tourism will also be explored by constructing an
underwater park and swim pool.
</P>
<P>
With Beijing-Qinhuangdao expressway as its impetus, the golden
tourism triangle of Beijing, Chengde and Qinhuangdao will be
opened to attract tourists from Beijing and Tianjin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
