<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's Police Ensure Violence-Free Local Poll </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, March 21 (Xinhua) -- At Least 30,000 policemen are
taking up their positions to ensure that today's local government
elections are not marred by violence, a police officer said.
</P>
<P>
He said the inspector general of police had given strict
instructions to all his men to take into custody anyone trying to
disrupt the election process or those attempting to sabotage the
vote.
</P>
<P>
Every police station has a riot squad at its command, the
strength of which depends on the size of the station. In major
towns like Colombo and Kandy riot squad manpower is greater,
compared to those in remote towns, he said.
</P>
<P>
The officer added that in addition to normal patrolling,
special mobile patrols are also being deployed.
</P>
<P>
The polling of the elections commenced at 7:00 a.m. today to
elect 238 local bodies, of which 12 are municipal councils, 31
urban councils and 195 village councils.  
</P>
</TEXT>
