<DOCNO> XIE19970321.0271 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Issue New Standards of Health Food </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 21 (Xinhua) -- China is to issue new state
standards for the production, marketing and administration of
health food from May 1, aiming to guide the fast-growing industry
in a sound direction.
</P>
<P>
The standards define the concept of health food, product
classification, general principles, technical requirements and
requirements on tags, said a report in today's "China Daily".
</P>
<P>
The standards were drafted last year by the National Technical
Committee of Standardization for the Health Food Industry and were
approved by the State Bureau of Technical Supervision last month.
</P>
<P>
They classify health food products into 13 categories according
to their effect on influencing human functions, while stressing
that health food is a special food not developed to cure diseases.
</P>
<P>
China witnessed a rapid growth of health food production in the
1990s, and the number of producers has reached about 3,000.
</P>
<P>
However, "they produced 3,000 different kinds of health food in
accordance with standards set by the enterprises themselves," the
newspaper quoted official sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
"Some of the health foods produce good effects on people's
health, but some have been found fake or inferior, and even
harmful to consumers," it said.
</P>
<P>
It said compulsory state standards will play an important role
in standardizing the health food market, improving supervision and
administration, safeguarding consumer interests and guiding
industry development in a sound direction.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
