<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NZ Milk Production to Set New Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, March 21 (Xinhua) -- New Zealand will handle an
extra 200,000 tons of milk in the current season ending June,
bringing total production to a record 1.2 million tons, the Dairy
Board estimates.
</P>
<P>
As a result, in the year to June, New Zealand will supply
nearly 30 percent of the international trade in dairy produce, up
from 22 percent in previous years, a local press report said
today.
</P>
<P>
The board expects to be able to sell virtually all the
additional milk this season, in contrast to last season when a
late surge in production left a carry-over stocks which had to be
disposed of by this year's sales.
</P>
<P>
However, the board noted that the huge and unexpected
production increase has meant that much of the extra milk has had
to be sold in the lower-price world commodity market, the report
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
