<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Albanian Passports Stolen by Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, March 20 (Xinhua) -- Albania is warning the United
States, Europe and neighboring states to be on the alert for
Albanians trying to enter their countries with forged diplomatic
passports.
</P>
<P>
The government issued the warning after a number of blank
Albanian diplomatic and service passports were stolen by rebels
from a storeroom in the Interior Ministry, an official said today.
</P>
<P>
The passports have been declared invalid and the government is
asking other countries to cooperate by detaining those using them.
</P>
<P>
Albania has also decided to temporarily suspend the issuing of
diplomatic and service passports.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of Albanians have fled the country over the past two
weeks to escape the violence and chaos caused by an armed uprising
which has swept the nation over the past weeks.
</P>
<P>
The unrest erupted after the collapse of popular pyramid
investment schemes in which thousands of Albanians lost their life
savings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
