<HEADLINE> Russia, Holland Sign Military Cooperation Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 20 (Xinhua) -- Russia and Holland signed two
agreements on military cooperation today, which Russia's defense
minister described as conducive to removing the negative impact of
NATO's planned eastward expansion on European security.
</P>
<P>
The agreements were signed by Russian Defense Minister Igor
Rodionov and visiting Dutch Minister of Defense Joris Voorhoeve.
</P>
<P>
Details of the accords were not given, but Itar-Tass news
agency reported there was one agreement on Russia-Holland military
cooperation, and one on cooperation between the two countries'
defense ministries.
</P>
<P>
Following talks with Voorhoeve, Rodionov said the Russian
defense ministry is preparing to further bilateral and
multilateral relations with those countries which understand
Russia and are willing to cooperate with Russia.
</P>
<P>
Voorhoeve said that all European countries should cooperate
with each other to establish a new system of European security.
</P>
<P>
Holland and Russia could cooperate on the issues of destroying
weapons of mass destruction and safeguarding peace in Europe, he
added.
</P>
<P>
Voorhoeve arrived in Moscow on Wednesday on a four-day official
visit to Russia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
