<HEADLINE> Israel to Hold Trade Exhibition in Ukraine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, March 20 (Xinhua) -- Some 80 Israeli companies will
gather in the Ukrainian capital Kiev on April 14 for a three-day
trade exhibition on Israeli telecommunications, agricultural and
medical technology.
</P>
<P>
Hana Kapitolink, managing director of Anzata International, the
Israeli company organizing the exhibition, Israel Only '97, said
70 percent of the exhibitors are entirely new to the Ukrainian
market.
</P>
<P>
She said no exhibitors would come from Israel's military
industrial sectors, though some of them supply parts to larger
companies involved in military production.
</P>
<P>
Two days before the exhibition starts, Nathan Sharanski,
Israel's Ukrainian-born Minister of Trade and Industry, will start
a four-day official visit to Russia. He will attend a meeting of
the Joint Committee on Ukrainian-Israel Trade on April 14.
</P>
<P>
Statistics provided by the Israeli Embassy indicated that more
than 100 Israeli joint ventures are now operating in Ukraine. The
total volume of Ukrainian-Israeli trade was 107 million
U.S. dollars in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Israeli Embassy First Secretary Edward Chapira said that about
300,000 Ukrainian immigrants living in Israel should act as a
bridge between the two countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
