<HEADLINE> East China City Hosts Tulip Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, March 21 (Xinhua) -- A tulip show started Wednesday
in Hangzhou, the capital of east China's Zhejiang province,
featuring 350,000 tulips of more than 80 different species.
</P>
<P>
Dutch tulips were introduced into Taiziwan Park near the city's
scenic spot of West Lake in 1992, and the park began an annual
tulip show in the spring in 1993.
</P>
<P>
More than 20 species were introduced into China for the first
time at the show.
</P>
<P>
Half the tulips are in bloom, according to Tang Xiaomin,
director of the park, who is trying to see to it that the tulip
blossoms can be seen for the entirety of the month-long show.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
