<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Stojko Wins Men's Title in Figure Skating Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAUSANNE, March 20 (Xinhua) -- Elvis Stojko of Canada, using a
quadruple-triple combination, rallied from fourth place to regain
the men's title at the World Figure Skating Championship here on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Stojko's task was made easier when Alexei Urmanov of Russia,
who led after Wednesday's short program, withdrew after warming up
due to a groin injury he suffered in practice.
</P>
<P>
Todd Eldredge of the United States, the defending champion,
came in second after faltering on two jumps late in his program.
</P>
<P>
Alexei Yagudin of Russia, 17, finished third.
</P>
<P>
Stojko completed the quad-triple combination and added seven
more triple jumps in a routine that earned him a perfect 6.0 from
one judge.
</P>
<P>
The rest of his marks were either 5.9 or 5.8 as Stojko gained
back the title he won in 1994 and 1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
