<HEADLINE> Eight Cuban Soliders, One Civilian Killed in Bus Collision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, March 20 (Xinhua) -- Eight soldiers and a civilian were
killed and 24 injured on Wednesday evening in a head-on collision
between a Cuban military bus and a truck.
</P>
<P>
The accident happened on the Holguin-Mayari highway 750
kilometers east of Havana, the army said last night.
</P>
<P>
The eight soldiers were members of the Eastern Army of the
Cuban Revolutionary Armed Forces.
</P>
<P>
The injured were taken to the nearby Lenin Hospital and the
Holguin military hospital.
</P>
<P>
Army authorities are investigating the cause of the accident.
</P>
