<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Polling Starts in Sri Lanka's Local Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's local government
elections commenced at 7:00 a.m. (local times) to elect 238 local
government bodies, of which 12 are municipal councils, 31 urban
councils and 195 village councils.
</P>
<P>
The elections are being held throughout the country except in
Northern and Eastern Provinces where a civil war is going on
between the government troops and the Tamil rebels who are
fighting a 14-year-old war for a separate state there.
</P>
<P>
There are a total of 9,737,970 voters and 8,244 polling
centers. A total of 18,586 candidates from 12 political parties
and 136 independent groups are vying for 3,567 seats in these
local bodies in the seven provinces.
</P>
<P>
Observers here believed that the main battle will be fought
between the ruling People's Alliance (PA) and the main opposition
United National Party (UNP).  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970321.0286 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> PSG Reaches Cup Winners' Cup Semis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 20 (Xinhua/OANA) -- Defending champion Paris
St. Germain of France, held to a 0-0 draw two weeks ago at home in
the first leg, reached the Cup Winners' Cup semi-finals with three
goals by Patrice Loko in a 3-0 victory over AEK Athens on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In Thursday's three other second-leg quarter-finals of the Cup
Winners' Cup: Liverpool of England routed Norway's Sk Brann 3-0 to
advance 4-1; Spain's Barcelona drew 1-1 with Sweden's AIK
Stockholm to go through 4-2; Italy's Fiorentina lost 1-0 at home
to Portugal's Benfica but still advanced 2-1.
</P>
<P>
The semi-final draw is to be conducted on Friday. The
first-leg semi-finals are April 10 with the second leg April 24.
The final is May 14 in Rotterdam, Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
In Athens, Loko put the French side ahead in the 22nd minute
and got his second goal two minutes left at the first half.
</P>
<P>
Loko wrapped up the victory with his third goal in the 80th
minute, beating a Greek defender on the dribble and then getting
the ball in behind Athens goalkeeper Ilias Atmatzidis.
</P>
<P>
In Liverpool, England, Robbie Fowler scored twice to bring his
season total to 28 and Stan Collymore got the other as the English
side defeated Norway's Brann 3-0 to advance 4-1.
</P>
<P>
In Florence, Italy, Angolan Edgar Pacheco scored in the 22nd
for Benfica in the 1-0 victory. But Fiorentina still went through
2-1.
</P>
<P>
In Stockholm, Sweden, Barcelona drew 1-1 to reach the
semi-finals on a 4-2 aggregate. World Footballer Ronaldo of
Brazil scored for Barcelona in the 13th minute and Pascal Simpson
of AIK Stockholm tied the game in the 73rd minute. 
</P>
