<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xiamen's Tourism Industry Growing Fast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, March 21 (Xinhua) -- A third of a million overseas
tourists visiting the coastal city of Xiamen in east China's
Fujian Province last year.
</P>
<P>
A total of 337,100 overseas tourists visited the seaside
resort, and spent 222 million US dollars there, 39.38 percent more
than for the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The city, which has had double-digital growth in the industry
for 15 years running, decided that tourism be made a pillar
industry last year. It is now one of the top ten tourist cities in
China, and has 60 hotels and some 7,000 rooms for overseas
tourists, as well as 45 travel agencies, with over 20,000 people
working in the tourist sector, and 200 such entertainment
facilities in the form of dance halls, karaoke bars, bowling
alleys, and health centers.
</P>
<P>
A series of tourism promotion activities will be held in the
city this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
