<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seville to Host 1999 Athletics Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 20 (Xinhua) -- Seville was selected on Thursday by
the International Amateur Athletic Federation (IAAF) to host the
1999 World Championships Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The 27-member IAAF Council made the decision in Turin, opting
for the Spanish city over three other contenders: Stanford,
California; New Delhi, India; and Helsinki, Finland.
</P>
<P>
Seville, which hosted the 1991 indoor championships, failed to
reach the short-list for the 2004 Olympic Games two weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
Seville does not currently have a stadium suitable for the
world outdoor championships, but began construction on an 85
million dollars, 60,000-seat facility last month. The stadium
will be finished in December 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
