<DOCNO> XIE19970321.0310 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cameroun Celebrates Intl Day of Francophonie </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, March 20 (Xinhua) -- Cameroun has launched week-long
celebrations to mark the International Day of the Francophonie
today which is observed worldwide on March 20.
</P>
<P>
The celebrations, starting from March 14, include a nationwide
radio quiz on general knowledge on the francophonie, roundtables,
exhibitions and other activities aimed at attracting people to
learn the cultural riches of the French speaking society.
</P>
<P>
The francophonie refers to the countries using French as their
common language.
</P>
<P>
The International Day of the Francophonie is seen as an
opportunity for French-speaking countries to install values of the
French language through art, sculpture, literature and
architecture. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
